cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper involves computer vision (CV) techniques for autonomous driving, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on model predictive control (MPC) for autonomous driving, which falls under the cs.RO (robotics) sub-category. The use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for predicting cost functions suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (machine learning) sub-category. The application of AI techniques for autonomous driving further supports the possibility of the paper belonging to the cs.AI sub-category. Finally, the use of MPC for trajectory optimization suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.SY (systems and control) sub-category.
